==Old Japanese==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*mə}}.

Appears in common use in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' (712 {{CE}}), with the only attested distinction between {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>1</sub>⟩}} and {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>2</sub>⟩}}. Compare {{cog|ltc|-}} {{ltc-l|母}}.

Pronunciation was distinct from {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>1</sub>⟩}} terms such as {{m|ojp|雲|tr=kumo<sub>1</sub>||[[cloud]]}} and {{m|ojp|下|tr=simo<sub>1</sub>||[[lower]], [[end]]}}; pronounced closely to {{cog|ltc|-}} {{ltc-l|毛}}. This was lost in a later ancient Japanese chronicle, the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' (720 {{CE}}), and {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>1</sub>⟩}} and {{IPAfont|⟨mo<sub>2</sub>⟩}} were merged to form one syllable ''mo''. See the {{w|Man'yōgana}} and {{w|Jōdai Tokushu Kanazukai}} articles for more detail on ancient spellings.

